(Tár panting)

2268
02:22:38,417 --> 02:22:41,153
DRIVER:
You sign CAMI voucher.

2269
02:22:41,186 --> 02:22:43,422
(driver speaking into phone
in Tamil)

2270
02:22:52,331 --> 02:22:54,566
(pile driver rattling
and thumping)

2271
02:23:01,841 --> 02:23:03,008
(phone rings in distance)

2272
02:23:03,042 --> 02:23:05,577
MAN:
Good afternoon. CAMI.

2273
02:23:05,611 --> 02:23:07,179
Hold on.

2274
02:23:08,147 --> 02:23:09,749
CORY:
Normally, I'd think Lisa Rich

2275
02:23:09,782 --> 02:23:12,384
in our booking department
would be a great fit for you,

2276
02:23:12,417 --> 02:23:14,620
but she's just got
too much on her plate.

2277
02:23:14,654 --> 02:23:18,257
So, I'd like to team you
with Jake here.

2278
02:23:18,290 --> 02:23:20,826
Jake, you want to,
you want to show Lydia

2279
02:23:20,860 --> 02:23:22,227
what you've prepared for her?

2280
02:23:22,261 --> 02:23:24,797
Well...

2281
02:23:24,830 --> 02:23:27,199
right now it's a reset.

2282
02:23:27,232 --> 02:23:29,001
What we're after is less,
not more.

2283
02:23:29,034 --> 02:23:30,235
We want to be selective

2284
02:23:30,269 --> 02:23:32,271
and rebuild this
from the ground up.

2285
02:23:32,304 --> 02:23:34,273
That means we need a new story.

2286
02:23:38,844 --> 02:23:40,646
TÁR:
Just here.

2287
02:23:40,680 --> 02:23:42,347
Here. Thank you.

2288
02:23:42,381 --> 02:23:44,216
(clears throat) Make it 40.

2289
02:23:44,249 --> 02:23:45,851
Thank you.

2290
02:23:53,893 --> 02:23:56,128
(sighs)

2291
02:24:05,070 --> 02:24:07,306
(piano plays note)

2292
02:24:08,307 --> 02:24:10,542
(piano playing discordant notes)

2293
02:24:14,646 --> 02:24:16,682
(music stops)

2294
02:24:53,318 --> 02:24:55,554
(sighs)

2295
02:25:00,826 --> 02:25:03,262
(orchestra playing
lively classical music over TV)

2296
02:25:18,110 --> 02:25:19,511
(music ends)

2297
02:25:19,544 --> 02:25:21,313
(over TV):
Didn't you feel triumphant?

2298
02:25:21,346 --> 02:25:23,582
(applause over TV)

2299
02:25:24,984 --> 02:25:28,720
Now we can really understand
what the meaning of music is.

2300
02:25:28,754 --> 02:25:32,825
It's the way it makes you feel
when you hear it.

2301
02:25:32,858 --> 02:25:35,928
Finally, we've taken
that last giant step.

2302
02:25:35,961 --> 02:25:38,630
And we're there.
We know what music means now.

2303
02:25:38,663 --> 02:25:41,466
And we don't have to know
a lot of stuff about sharps

2304
02:25:41,500 --> 02:25:43,936
and flats and chords
and all that business

2305
02:25:43,969 --> 02:25:48,874
in order to understand music
if it tells us something.

2306
02:25:48,908 --> 02:25:52,244
And the most wonderful thing of
all is that there's no limit to

2307
02:25:52,277 --> 02:25:56,681
the different kinds of feelings
music can make you have.

2308
02:25:56,715 --> 02:26:00,619
And some of those feelings
are so special and so deep

2309
02:26:00,652 --> 02:26:03,088
that they can't even be
described in words.

2310
02:26:03,122 --> 02:26:04,456
You see, we can't always name

2311
02:26:04,489 --> 02:26:05,858
-the things we feel.
-(sobs softly)

2312
02:26:05,891 --> 02:26:06,926
Sometimes we can.

2313
02:26:06,959 --> 02:26:08,460
We can say we feel joy,

2314
02:26:08,493 --> 02:26:12,231
pleasure, peacefulness,
whatever, love, hate.

2315
02:26:12,264 --> 02:26:14,499
But every once in a while,

2316
02:26:14,533 --> 02:26:17,336
we have feelings that are
so deep and so special

2317
02:26:17,369 --> 02:26:18,904
that we have no words for them.

2318
02:26:18,938 --> 02:26:22,107
And that's where music
is so marvelous,

2319
02:26:22,141 --> 02:26:24,409
because music names them for us,

2320
02:26:24,443 --> 02:26:27,279
only in notes
instead of in words.

2321
02:26:27,312 --> 02:26:28,881
It's all in the way music moves.

2322
02:26:28,914 --> 02:26:31,616
You must never forget
that music is movement,

2323
02:26:31,650 --> 02:26:34,453
always going somewhere,
shifting and changing

2324
02:26:34,486 --> 02:26:38,290
and flowing
from one note to another.

2325
02:26:38,323 --> 02:26:39,791
-(crying)
-And that movement can tell us

2326
02:26:39,825 --> 02:26:42,895
more about the way we feel
than a million words can.

2327
02:26:42,928 --> 02:26:44,629
And here we're going
to play you a...

2328
02:26:44,663 --> 02:26:46,999
-(VCR clicks)
-(whimpers)

2329
02:26:49,668 --> 02:26:51,703
(door opens in distance)

2330
02:26:51,736 --> 02:26:53,738
(exhales sharply, sniffles)

2331
02:26:59,211 --> 02:27:00,880
Tony.

2332
02:27:02,181 --> 02:27:03,849
Oh.

2333
02:27:03,883 --> 02:27:05,084
Hi, Linda.

2334
02:27:05,117 --> 02:27:06,318
Sorry.

2335
02:27:06,351 --> 02:27:08,553
Lydia.

2336
02:27:08,587 --> 02:27:11,090
Ma said you'd be over.

2337
02:27:11,123 --> 02:27:13,458
You must be hiding out.

2338
02:27:14,259 --> 02:27:16,661
Why would I be hiding out?

2339
02:27:16,695 --> 02:27:19,064
Beats the hell out of me.

2340
02:27:19,098 --> 02:27:21,333
None of my business anyhow.

2341
02:27:22,467 --> 02:27:24,937
Lot of loose ends,
you got to admit.

2342
02:27:26,471 --> 02:27:27,940
What do you mean?

2343
02:27:27,973 --> 02:27:30,275
Well, like I said,
it ain't my business.

2344
02:27:31,276 --> 02:27:33,645
But you don't seem to know
where the hell you came from

2345
02:27:33,678 --> 02:27:35,547
or where you're going.

2346
02:27:40,419 --> 02:27:42,654
(woman speaking Thai over P.A.)

2347
02:27:48,360 --> 02:27:50,595
(water runs, stops)

2348
02:28:10,382 --> 02:28:12,617
(traffic passing)

2349
02:28:18,323 --> 02:28:21,060
(rooster crowing)

2350
02:28:21,093 --> 02:28:22,962
(car horn honking)

2351
02:28:27,666 --> 02:28:29,601
May I come inside?

2352
02:28:30,869 --> 02:28:32,504
Thank you.

2353
02:28:34,173 --> 02:28:37,409
(conversing in Tagalog)

2354
02:28:44,449 --> 02:28:46,118
Um, I'm so sorry.

2355
02:28:46,151 --> 02:28:48,753
Uh, we just wanted to confirm
that the composer was in fact

2356
02:28:48,787 --> 02:28:50,822
not flying in from Osaka
to attend the concert.

2357
02:28:50,855 --> 02:28:52,257
Oh.

2358
02:28:52,291 --> 02:28:55,394
I-I must tell you that I-I
looked in the music libraries,

2359
02:28:55,427 --> 02:28:59,364
uh, for her score,
but I-I couldn't find anything.

2360
02:28:59,398 --> 02:29:01,566
-This just arrived.
-Ah.

2361
02:29:01,600 --> 02:29:03,835
That's great. Thank you.

2362
02:29:05,070 --> 02:29:07,606
Shirley and Cirio will be
most happy to show you

2363
02:29:07,639 --> 02:29:09,674
-the sights of our beautiful
country. -Oh. Thank you.

2364
02:29:09,708 --> 02:29:11,510
Thank you so much.

2365
02:29:11,543 --> 02:29:13,645
Oh, goodness.

2366
02:29:13,678 --> 02:29:15,547
Thank-thank you.

2367
02:29:21,320 --> 02:29:24,056
(man howls)

2368
02:29:39,371 --> 02:29:41,606
(motor rattling quietly)

2369
02:29:46,711 --> 02:29:50,682
Maybe we could stop somewhere
and take a swim.

2370
02:29:50,715 --> 02:29:52,484
Yeah, at the waterfall.

2371
02:29:52,517 --> 02:29:54,386
But, mm, not in the river.

2372
02:29:54,419 --> 02:29:57,189
Why? Is there something wrong
with the water?

2373
02:29:57,222 --> 02:29:59,891
N-No. There are crocodiles.

2374
02:29:59,924 --> 02:30:01,893
Oh.

2375
02:30:01,926 --> 02:30:04,496
I didn't think
they'd be this far inland.

2376
02:30:04,529 --> 02:30:07,399
They escaped from
Marlon Brando movie.

2377
02:30:07,432 --> 02:30:09,168
Wow.

2378
02:30:09,201 --> 02:30:12,104
That was a long time ago.

2379
02:30:12,137 --> 02:30:13,905
They survive.

2380
02:30:19,911 --> 02:30:22,147
(playful screaming, laughter)

2381
02:30:28,587 --> 02:30:30,822
(Shirley whoops)

2382
02:30:30,855 --> 02:30:33,092
(Shirley and Cirio laughing)

2383
02:30:40,565 --> 02:30:43,802
(men speaking Tagalog, kissing)

2384
02:30:48,173 --> 02:30:50,609
-Lady. Lady.
-(chatter continues) -(kissing)

2385
02:30:52,611 --> 02:30:53,945
Here is prescription.

2386
02:30:53,978 --> 02:30:55,647
-Ten dollars.
-Oh. Thank you.

2387
02:30:55,680 --> 02:30:57,082
(pills rattle)

2388
02:30:57,116 --> 02:31:01,386
Uh, is there somewhere
around here-- thank you--

2389
02:31:01,420 --> 02:31:03,288
where I could get a massage?

2390
02:31:03,322 --> 02:31:06,057
Was hoping it might help me
with this jet lag.

2391
02:31:06,091 --> 02:31:08,059
(sighs)

2392
02:31:08,093 --> 02:31:10,061
Hmm.

2393
02:31:10,095 --> 02:31:11,163
Yes.

2394
02:31:11,196 --> 02:31:14,133
There is
the very nice place I know.

2395
02:31:14,166 --> 02:31:15,934
Thank you.

2396
02:31:15,967 --> 02:31:18,203
(relaxing music playing
over speakers)

2397
02:31:29,013 --> 02:31:30,115
Thank you.

2398
02:31:30,149 --> 02:31:32,184
Please step over
to the fishbowl.

2399
02:31:32,217 --> 02:31:34,052
The... the fishbowl?

2400
02:31:34,085 --> 02:31:35,787
Yes, over there.

2401
02:31:41,092 --> 02:31:42,661
Um, I'm sorry, I'm confused.

2402
02:31:42,694 --> 02:31:44,863
H-How does this...
how does it work?

2403
02:31:45,697 --> 02:31:47,899
You just pick a number here.

2404
02:31:49,268 --> 02:31:51,370
I pick a number?

2405
02:31:51,403 --> 02:31:53,004
Yes.

2406
02:31:53,037 --> 02:31:54,606
(chuckles)

2407
02:32:03,915 --> 02:32:06,151
RECEPTIONIST:
Number five?

2408
02:32:11,590 --> 02:32:13,658
(gasps)

2409
02:32:18,663 --> 02:32:20,565
(gagging)

2410
02:32:20,599 --> 02:32:22,834
(retching)

2411
02:32:25,003 --> 02:32:26,371
(groans)

2412
02:32:26,405 --> 02:32:27,972
(panting)

2413
02:32:34,579 --> 02:32:36,815
(music playing quietly over TV)

2414
02:32:43,655 --> 02:32:45,890
(woman speaking Tagalog)

2415
02:32:49,561 --> 02:32:51,129
Good morning.

2416
02:32:51,162 --> 02:32:52,864
MUSICIANS:
Good morning.

2417
02:32:52,897 --> 02:32:55,267
Now, before we begin,
let's-let's talk a bit about

2418
02:32:55,300 --> 02:32:59,003
the composer's intent
with this piece.

2419
02:33:00,171 --> 02:33:02,374
And what she might be after.

2420
02:33:02,407 --> 02:33:04,175
(busy chatter)

2421
02:33:04,209 --> 02:33:06,645
(pop music playing
over speakers)

2422
02:33:21,159 --> 02:33:23,194
-(sighs)
-MAN: Five minutes.

2423
02:33:24,729 --> 02:33:26,965
(instruments warming up
in distance)

2424
02:33:31,503 --> 02:33:33,738
(panting softly)

2425
02:33:35,507 --> 02:33:37,175
(gasps)

2426
02:33:37,208 --> 02:33:38,543
(exhales sharply)

2427
02:33:38,577 --> 02:33:40,812
(applause)

2428
02:33:49,554 --> 02:33:51,790
(applause swells)

2429
02:33:54,759 --> 02:33:56,761
-Thank you.
-(applause fades)

2430
02:34:04,636 --> 02:34:06,471
(mechanical whirring)

2431
02:34:10,875 --> 02:34:12,444
(whirring stops)

2432
02:34:15,680 --> 02:34:18,750
(fabric rustling over speakers)

2433
02:34:18,783 --> 02:34:20,552
(orchestra playing gentle music)

2434
02:34:20,585 --> 02:34:24,689
ANNOUNCER: Sisters and brothers
of the Fifth Fleet, it's time.

2435
02:34:24,723 --> 02:34:27,091
I'll keep my farewell brief.

2436
02:34:27,125 --> 02:34:29,861
Never was much with words.

2437
02:34:29,894 --> 02:34:33,832
Once you board this ship,
there's no turning back.

2438
02:34:33,865 --> 02:34:38,303
The next ground your feet touch
will be that of the New World.

2439
02:34:38,337 --> 02:34:40,772
(music building)

2440
02:34:40,805 --> 02:34:42,807
If any of you
have lost your nerve,

2441
02:34:42,841 --> 02:34:46,978
then step away now
and let no one judge you.

2442
02:34:47,011 --> 02:34:49,247
(music fades)

2443
02:34:55,354 --> 02:34:57,389
*

2444
02:35:25,517 --> 02:35:27,552
*

2445
02:35:52,276 --> 02:35:53,912
*

2446
02:36:21,740 --> 02:36:23,975
*

2447
02:36:53,772 --> 02:36:56,007
*

2448
02:37:22,601 --> 02:37:24,636
*

2449
02:37:52,163 --> 02:37:54,398
*

2450
02:38:04,709 --> 02:38:06,711
(music ends)
